Gatara checks her own sensor readouts to see what was going on.  
"Blast it!" she snarls.  "Jayde, one of these days you're going to 
get yourself killed.  Riekan!  Hold down the fort here, Torin and I 
are going after her."

"Correction," says a voice from the doorway.  "You're holding down 
the fort, while Riekan, Torin and I do the running around."

"Devilcat!  You're awake!"  Even Riekan is shocked, a real difficult 
thing to to.

"Exactly," Devilcat grunts.  "No thanks to that bit of weather we ran 
across.  You can give me the story on the way, guys.  Let's go!"

Gatara doesn't argue, even though she's itching for combat.  She 
knows full well she's the slowest of the Rogues, and this mission 
calls for speed.  Sighing, she watches the boys zoom off, cloaking as 
they go, then reactivates the cloaking device on Rogue Star itself.
